<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1910-05-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1910-05-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="945" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d945">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Chargé <persName type="from">Tarler</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Bangkok</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-05-28"><hi rend="italic">May 28,
                                1910</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 608.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inclose herewith in
                            duplicate copy<note n="1" xml:id="d945fn1">Not printed.</note> of a
                            translation of the supplementary law to the law on navigation in Siamese
                            waters (R. S. 124), which will be put into force on August 1 next. I
                            have been requested to make the same binding on all American citizens in
                            Siam.</p>
                        <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">G. Cornell
                            Tarler.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>